A web-based IDE for PML

Contents:
1. Features
2. Setup
 
Features:
	- File upload
	- Syntax analysis
	- File save & retrieve
	- Authentication
	- Code editor
	- Syntax highlighting
	- Code completion (keywords and resources)
	- Editor keybinding emulation
	- Error highlighting

Setup:
These instructions are for installing this software on Ubuntu 14.04 64-bit.

Ensure the required packages are installed:
	./install_dependencies.sh

Choose a project name and deploy the IDE:
	sudo ./install.sh projectName

Check that the installation went OK:
	./verify_installation.sh projectName

Access the IDE by visiting localhost/projectName

Remove the IDE at any time by running:
	sudo ./clean.sh projectName

